The paper deals with efficient packet combining techniques for coded transmission over a MIMO channel with ISI, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of automatic repeat request (ARQ) protocols, which is a topic related to system implementation (cs.SI). The paper proposes two algorithms for turbo packet combining, which involves signal processing (cs.MM) and communication systems (cs.COM).
